item.title: Reading .class files?
item.dc:creator: @chassy13 Chassy13
item.description:
@chassy13 wrote:

I am guessing you are using a 508. The class files and java files are seperated into different folders. If I remember correctly, the java files are in the ‘src’ folder. The only way you can “edit” class files is to use a decompiler and convert the class file back into the java file. You can find many decompilers using a simple Google search. If you mess up the bytecode in the actual class file, it will just ruin it.
